Package DataModel.LocationData

Class FavLocation

java.lang.Object
DataModel.LocationData.FavLocation
public class FavLocation
extends java.lang.Object
Class: java.DataModel.LocationData.FavLocation This class stores a location that the user has assigned as one of their favorite locations, a favorite location consists of a location and a type. The location will be from the datatype Location, whereas the type is a String that specifies the type of the location stored.

the information of this class will be filled in the MainSystem. The FavLocation class has only one constructor that takes a Location and a String, representing the type of the location, and creates a FavLocation with that location and that type. Moreover, this class also offers a method called containLocation which takes a Location in its parameter and compare it to the location stored in the FavLocation that called this method, it returns a Boolean that will be true if the two locations are the same, and false if not.

However, this class offers setters and getters to access and modify its attributes which we use in the MainSystem in order to give the user the possibility to edit their favorite locationâ€™s type. In other words, if the user assign a location as their favorite location, then they try to assign the same place as their favorite location again, the will not be able to, but they will be able to change the type of their already assigned favorite location
